The article commemorates the 75th anniversary of the end of World War II in Europe. It pays tribute to the Allied forces who defeated the Nazi regime and celebrates the forces of freedom. It acknowledges the high cost of freedom, with over 30 million lives lost and millions more affected. The article highlights the sacrifices made by American soldiers, with over 186,000 deaths and twice that number wounded. It emphasizes that these soldiers came from diverse backgrounds and were motivated by their belief in American principles. The article also draws parallels between the challenges faced during World War II and the current adversity of the coronavirus pandemic, expressing confidence that America will triumph and emerge stronger. The author expresses gratitude towards the remaining World War II veterans, known as the Greatest Generation, for their contributions to the nation's success and prosperity.